Description: ScreenPad 2.0 control for the ASUS ZenBook UX435EG
 Userspace tool + systemd unit for driving the ScreenPad 2.0 secondary panel
 on the ASUS ZenBook UX435EG (Tiger Lake, BIOS UX435EG.315). Talks to the ATK
 WMI method \_SB.ATKD.WMNB via acpi_call, bypassing the mainline asus_wmi
 driver which does not bind the management GUID on this BIOS and leaves the
 panel dark.
 .
 Provides:
   * /usr/local/bin/ux435-screenpad - power on/off and set brightness (0..255)
   * a oneshot systemd service that restores state at boot
   * a udev rule granting the video group write access to the backlight node
     (if a future kernel ever creates it)
   * a diagnose script that dumps everything needed for a bug report
 .
 This is a workaround, not a proper driver. See docs/ for the reverse
 engineering notes.
